Eddie, Chris:
Just not tight enough to begin with. Look it up, use a torque wrench. It's way tighter than
you can get by hand with a simple L-shaped wrench! I often have trouble breaking them loose
with an air wrench years later and it's not cause they are rusty, it's cause they are tight!
